The program must accept the time in
24-hour format. The program must print 
the time in 12-hour format as the output.

Example Input/Output:
Input:
0000

Output:
12:00 AM


ğŸ„°ğŸ„½ğŸ…‚ğŸ…†ğŸ„´ğŸ…

#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

int main()
{
int time, hours, minutes;
char period[3]="AM";
scanf("%d",&time);
hours=time/100;
minutes=time%100;
if(hours==0){
    hours=12;
}else if(hours==12){
    period[0]='P';
}else if(hours>12){
    hours -= 12;
    period[0]='P';
}
printf("%02d:%02d %s",hours,minutes,period);
}
